<paragraph blockId="30.[189,1399,1442,1504]" pageId="30" pageNumber="124">
A well defined, conceivably monophyletic tribe (
<bibRefCitation author="Couri M. S. &amp; Pont A. C." box="[784,1025,1442,1469]" pageId="30" pageNumber="124" pagination="373 - 392" refId="ref13951" refString="Couri M. S. &amp; Pont A. C. 2000. Cladistic analysis of Coenosiini (Diptera: Muscidae). Systematic Entomology 25: 373 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1365 - 3113.2000.00125. x" type="journal article" year="2000">Couri &amp; Pont 2000</bibRefCitation>
), currently with 34 recognized genera; species from 23 genera were examined (
<tableCitation box="[755,843,1477,1504]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="5.[189,258,265,291]" captionTargetBox="[238,1379,394,1980]" captionText="Table 1 (continued on next 4 pages). Summary of vein C chaetotaxy with respect to multistate characterA for genus-group taxa of Fanniidae Schnabel &amp; Dziedcicki, 1911 and Muscidae Latreille, 1802. Examined genera highlighted in yellow. See ‘Material and methods’ for explanation of character states A0–8." pageId="30" pageNumber="124">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
